    "Detailed hyperparamter settings are in Appendix A.",
    "We conduct extensive evaluations against models with similar sizes, including Sailor-7B / Sailor-7B-Chat (Dou et al., 2024), Gemma-7b / Gemma-7b-it (Mesnard et al., 2024), Qwen2-7B / Qwen2-7B-Chat (Yang et al., 2024), Llama-3-8B / Llama-3-8B-Instruct (Touvron et al., 2023b), Aya-23-8B (Aryabumi et al., 2024), and the previous versions (mainly v2.5) of SeaLLMs (Nguyen et al., 2023c).",
    "The evaluations can be generally categorized into the following two dimensions: (1) Model Capability: We assess the model's performance on human exam questions, its ability to follow multiturn instructions, its proficiency in mathematics, and its translation accuracy of different language pairs; (2) Model Trustworthiness: We evaluate the model's safety and tendency to hallucinate, particularly in the context of Southeast Asia.",
    "4.1 Model Capability Evaluation 4.1.1 Multilingual World Knowledge",
    "Dataset We utilize the M3Exam dataset (Zhang et al., 2023), comprising real human exam questions collected from different countries and spanning different subjects and educational stages."
